title: JUI-P’s Aftab Haider wins PK-111 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat-Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) candidate Makhdoomzada Muhammad Aftab Haider has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-111 Dera Ismail Khan-I by securing 41,052 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf Parliamentarian (PTI-P) candidate Ehtsham Javed who bagged 37,008 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 60.98 per cent.
